  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Adam Smith International (ASI) Building Capacity to use Research Evidence in Sierra Leone, Liberia and South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve the ability of African governments to make collective Cabinet decisions that are evidence based, through providing specialist training to Cabinet secretariats, ministers and government officials. This will benefit Cabinet ministers through providing them with the skills and support to assess whether policy proposals have been based on evidence.  This contributes to our MDGs by helping developing countries to design more effective national policies that will better contribute to national development goals and poverty reduction.</narrative>
  </description>
